<br>
Melees at 50+ usually have at least 2k or so in weapons. Maybe 10k worth. The next step up from what the average mid 50s melee is using is usually insanely expensive. For example, I'm using Swiftwind (offhand epic) and a Lupine Dagger (9/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Obviously, magicians aren't going to be summoning anything that beats swiftwind, so just talk about the puppy dagger. The next step up from that would be Ornate Sword of the General (10/18 +stats no drop), Fayguard Parrying Dagger (9/17 10ac no drop), Guard Captains Mallet (11/20 +stats +HP tradeable) or Toxiferous Axe (10/17 +stats +HP tradeable). The dagger goes for around 2k on xegony. The mallet would be a 3% increase in main hand damage (so a 1.5-2% overall increase), and costs about 6500pp. The tox axe would be a 13% increase in main hand damage, and runs around 30k.<br>
<br>
How good should these summons be? If they're going to be as good as a lupine dagger (2k range), they won't be worth summoning most of the time. If they're as good as a guard captains mallet, they'll be worth summoning a lot of the time, but will have a smaller impact on damage output than putting on a focus bracer. If they're as good as a tox axe, then they'd be worth banking on a corpse when you log off, and tracking down a magician when you log in without it.<br>
<br>
It's how the economy works, and it's why tradeskills either make utter crap, or are controlled by hard to get components. Magician summons are near zero cost. If people find them useful, they will not use anything that's inferior, because it's a lot harder to go camp anything than track down a magician to summon it.<br>
<br>
The only situation that summon weapons would work well is special purpose weapons. Weapons with bane damage, elemental damage, procs that only hit certain types of mobs, and so on. <p><center>
